rComments: Enjoyable, though slow, lectures. Watts is incredibly well-read and intelligent, though does not possess the charisma necessary to command such a large lecture hall. If I hadn't enjoyed the subject matter so much, he likely would not have held my interest, though he tries very hard to please the students.
Good guy, but a little boring

Watts was a professor who clearly enjoyed what he was teaching. The nature of the material was pretty dry, but he tried in his own somewhat nerdy way to make it more interesting. Overall, a really nice prof.
Nice guy but doesn't really stand out as a professor, especially among the other 3 introductory ANT professors - he just comes and goes. Easiest section of the intro to Anthro course.

It's hard to follow after Lehman; I took him for granted while he was our instuctor for the Arch section, but for the mid-term and final, his m/c section practically saved most of the class from failing.
It's hard for anyone to make archeology interesting, he is no exception. Good class to catch up on sleep, I don't even need to try to fall asleep.

EXCELLENT PROF... one of the best profs i ever had.. he is extremely helpful.. his tests are all MC and requires memorization.. He is an excelleeeeent prof.. i am glad i took this course.. if you do well in ur tests .. u can get a 4.0 no doubt about it :)
Super patient and understanding professor. He was just filling in for banning last year in archaeological lab but he is teaching Archaeology of Eastern North America this spring. take it!
